  <h1 class="article__title">Accessibility Statement</h1>

  <h2>Commitment</h2>
  <p>
    I'm committed to making this website accessible to everyone.
    The site targets conformance with <strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA</strong> and is continuously improved based on testing and feedback.
  </p>

  <h2>What we do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Semantic HTML for clear document structure and landmarks</li>
    <li>Full keyboard navigation across all interactive elements</li>
    <li>A skip-to-content link for bypassing navigation</li>
    <li>Sufficient color contrast ratios across light and dark themes</li>
    <li>Screen reader support with ARIA labels and roles where needed</li>
    <li>Respect for <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> — animations are disabled automatically for users who prefer reduced motion</li>
    <li>A settings panel to manually disable particles, motion effects, and the custom cursor</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Known limitations</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Custom cursor</strong> — A decorative custom cursor replaces the default on desktop. It can be disabled via the settings panel or is automatically hidden on touch devices.</li>
    <li><strong>Canvas particles</strong> — A decorative particle effect runs on a background canvas element. It is marked <code>aria-hidden</code> and can be disabled via settings.</li>
    <li><strong>Motion effects</strong> — Scroll-based animations and text effects are present throughout the site. These are automatically disabled when <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> is set in your operating system, and can also be toggled off in the settings panel.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Feedback</h2>
  <p>
    If you encounter any accessibility barriers on this site, I'd love to hear about it.
    Please reach out at <a href="mailto:inti@valderas.be">inti@valderas.be</a> and I'll do my best to address it.
  </p>

  <p class="article__updated">Last updated — March 2026</p>
